There is no such an option on a File Inbound Channel Adapter since we cannot remove files unconditionally - their content might be required downstream which may happen on a fully different thread from the poller.

We recommend to use a simple `File.delete()` execution as a service activator logic downstream the SFTP transferring channel adapter.

It might be even better to have a `PublishSubscribeChannel` as an input for your `SftpMessageHandler` subscriber and add another one as plain as this:

    @ServiceActivator(inputChannel = &quot;sftpChannel&quot;)
    public void deleteLocalFile(File payload) {   
       payload.delete();
    }

