answers.body_markdown:
The warning is actually based on whether it can find the configured `&lt;classesDirectory&gt;` - by default `target\classes`.

This means one simple way to bypass the warning is to point it at another deliberately empty directory:

	&lt;build&gt;
		&lt;plugins&gt;
			&lt;plugin&gt;
				&lt;artifactId&gt;maven-jar-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
				&lt;configuration&gt;
					&lt;classesDirectory&gt;dummy&lt;/classesDirectory&gt;
				&lt;/configuration&gt;
			&lt;/plugin&gt;
		&lt;/plugins&gt;
	&lt;/build&gt;

Alternatively, to avoid the need for the empty directory, exclude everything from another directory:

			&lt;plugin&gt;
				&lt;artifactId&gt;maven-jar-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
				&lt;configuration&gt;
					&lt;classesDirectory&gt;src&lt;/classesDirectory&gt;
					&lt;excludes&gt;
						&lt;exclude&gt;**&lt;/exclude&gt;
					&lt;/excludes&gt;
				&lt;/configuration&gt;
			&lt;/plugin&gt;

Both solutions suppressed the warning message programmatically.

Solution 1:
-----------

    &lt;!-- https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.apache.maven.plugins/maven-jar-plugin --&gt;
    &lt;plugin&gt;
    	&lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
    	&lt;artifactId&gt;maven-jar-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    	&lt;version&gt;3.1.0&lt;/version&gt;
    	&lt;!-- Ignore src/main in JAR packaging --&gt;
    	&lt;configuration&gt;
    		&lt;classesDirectory&gt;src&lt;/classesDirectory&gt;
    		&lt;excludes&gt;
    			&lt;exclude&gt;main&lt;/exclude&gt;
    		&lt;/excludes&gt;
    	&lt;/configuration&gt;
    &lt;/plugin&gt;


Solution 2:
-----------
Since the above essentially created an empty JAR (and I did not really want to include test classes and test resources), I opted to &quot;skip&quot; the JAR creation instead.

https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2188746/what-is-the-best-way-to-avoid-maven-jar

    &lt;plugin&gt;
    	&lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
    	&lt;artifactId&gt;maven-jar-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    	&lt;version&gt;3.1.0&lt;/version&gt;
    	&lt;executions&gt;
    		&lt;execution&gt;
    			&lt;id&gt;default-jar&lt;/id&gt;
    			&lt;phase&gt;none&lt;/phase&gt;
    		&lt;/execution&gt;
    	&lt;/executions&gt;
    &lt;/plugin&gt;

This is (according to me) the cleanest solution  
for projects that don&#39;t contain production code but do contain tests:

```xml
    &lt;build&gt;
        &lt;plugins&gt;
            &lt;plugin&gt;
                &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
                &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-jar-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
                &lt;configuration&gt;
                    &lt;skipIfEmpty&gt;true&lt;/skipIfEmpty&gt;
                &lt;/configuration&gt;
            &lt;/plugin&gt;
            &lt;plugin&gt;
                &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
                &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-install-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
                &lt;configuration&gt;
                    &lt;skip&gt;true&lt;/skip&gt;
                &lt;/configuration&gt;
            &lt;/plugin&gt;
            &lt;plugin&gt;
                &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
                &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-deploy-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
                &lt;configuration&gt;
                    &lt;skip&gt;true&lt;/skip&gt;
                &lt;/configuration&gt;
            &lt;/plugin&gt;
        &lt;/plugins&gt;
    &lt;/build&gt;
```

It indicates what you want:

 - to skip trying to package &quot;no production code&quot; into a jar
 - don&#39;t try to install/deploy the non-existing jar

leaving test execution untouched.

---

Like [@John Camerin][1] mentioned it is NOT advised to use `&lt;packaging&gt;pom&lt;/packaging&gt;`  
unless the ONLY thing your pom should do is gather dependencies.  
Otherwise, if you have tests, they would be skipped without warning, which is not what you want.

A shorter alternative
---

Some of these configuration parameters are tied to **user properties**:
- `maven-jar-plugin`&#39;s [`skipIfEmpty`][2] parameter sadly is not linked to any user property
- `maven-install-plugin`&#39;s [`skip`][3] parameter gets its value from `maven.install.skip`
- `maven-deploy-plugin`&#39;s [`skip`][4] parameter gets its value from `maven.deploy.skip`

This means the pom could be shortened to
```xml
    &lt;properties&gt;
        &lt;maven.install.skip&gt;true&lt;/maven.install.skip&gt;
        &lt;maven.deploy.skip&gt;true&lt;/maven.deploy.skip&gt;
    &lt;/properties&gt;

    &lt;build&gt;
        &lt;plugins&gt;
            &lt;plugin&gt;
                &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
                &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-jar-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
                &lt;configuration&gt;
                    &lt;skipIfEmpty&gt;true&lt;/skipIfEmpty&gt;
                &lt;/configuration&gt;
            &lt;/plugin&gt;
        &lt;/plugins&gt;
    &lt;/build&gt;
```

  [1]: https://stackoverflow.com/a/53017986/426371
  [2]: https://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-jar-plugin/jar-mojo.html#skipIfEmpty
  [3]: https://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-install-plugin/install-mojo.html#skip
  [4]: https://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-deploy-plugin/deploy-mojo.html#skip

